abstract.text: Monitor In-App Purchase events in real time and learn of unreported external purchase tokens, with server notifications from the App Store.
An object that contains information about the most recent in-app purchase transactions for the app.
An object that contains information about the latest in-app subscription transaction.
An array of elements that refers to open auto-renewable subscription renewals or ones that failed in the past.
Sets a UUID to associate the purchase with an account in your system.
A string that associates the transaction with a user account on your service.
A request to the App Store to process payment for additional functionality that your app offers.
A string used to identify a product that can be purchased from within your app.
The number of items the user wants to purchase.
The payment for the transaction.
The date the transaction was added to the App Store’s payment queue.
Information about a registered product in App Store Connect.
The identifier of the subscription group to which the subscription belongs.
A UUID that associates the transaction with a user on your own service.
The time and date that the App Store refunds a transaction or revokes it from Family Sharing.
The time, in milliseconds, a subscription expires or renews.
The relationship of the user with the family-shared purchase to which they have access.
An indicator of whether an auto-renewable subscription is in the introductory price period.
An indicator of whether an auto-renewable subscription is in the free trial period.
The offer-reference name of the subscription offer code that the customer redeems.
The transaction identifier of the original purchase.
The identifier of the promotional offer for an auto-renewable subscription that the user redeems.
A unique identifier for a transaction, such as a purchase, restore, or renewal.
